title.45: Sgt. Fury and His Howling Commandos Annual (1965) #4

description.0: A dinner party with Peter Parker and Norman Osborn in attendance goes awry when the pair's alternate personas get the best of them.
description.1: Stranded in the Savage Land! Between dodging dinosaurs, Bruce Banner must race to find a dangerous artifact that threatens Earth's axis. And since it's a Savage Land story, it wouldn't be complete without saying: guest-starring Ka-Zar!
description.2: The Jester's rampant lies have tarnished Daredevil's name, but now it's time for Matt Murdock to turn the tables on the fiend! It's no laughing matter, as Murdock comes up with a devilish plot to unmask the Jester. But can DD protect his own identity...on national TV?
description.3: The baby is coming! With Sue going into labor, Reed must make a perilous journey to obtain Element X, the only thing that can keep the baby safe from the cosmic rays in Sue's body. The bad news - it can only be found in the Negative Zone! The WORSE news? It's in the hands of one of the deadliest beings in any universe - ANNIHILUS!
description.4: Iron Man's back is against the ropes, as he finds himself at the mercy of the Gladiator's whirling blades. Can Tony Stark save his friends from certain death? Find out when the Maggia strikes!
description.6: Thor returns to Earth under the guise of Donald Blake. Contemplative after his battle with Mangog, Thor reflects on his dual life as mortal and god. Who is Thor? Is he Donald Blake, a mortal granted divine powers? Or a true God of Thunder, the son of Odin?
description.8: The terror of Tomazooma! Reed, Johnny and Ben encounter an android designed after an Indian god while visiting Wyatt Wingfoot's tribe. But Tomazooma is no protector- he's a tyrant!
description.9: Dane Whitman is harboring doubts about his super-hero identity, Black Knight. After encountering the spirit of Sir Percy of Scandia, Whitman realizes that he may be a worthy possessor of the title after all.
description.12: Silver Surfer's naptime is interrupted by a meteor shower...and later -- a Badoon invasion!
description.13: The Sorcerer Supreme is caught in the midst of a mystical sibling rivalry when he's used as a pawn by Umar against her brother Dormammu!
description.15: The Battle for the High Seas! Who will prove to be stronger, the Sub-Mariner or Tiger Shark?!
description.16: The menace of the Mandarin continues! What is his secret plan, and how does it involve the Hulk? You won't want to miss this explosive climax!
description.17: Mar-Vell discovers Dr. Norman Lundquist's Solar Amplification Light-Cannon has the potential to create a solar energy creature - and it does just that!
description.18: In his first ever annual, an outcast Hulk attempts to demolish the Inhumans and their Royal Family!
description.19: Daredevil has been framed for the Jester's murder, and now all of New York City is after Ol' Hornhead! As a defender of the law, will Matt Murdock know when to bow out? No chance! Daredevil's identity is challenged by the public- and a more private audience.
description.20: Iron Man finds himself in a fight to the death when the Crusher cries vengeance!
description.22: Balder the Brave, Warrior Prince of Asgard, versus the mighty Mangog! Will an entire army of Asgardian soldiers be enough to thwart the coming of Ragnarok? Find out in the explosive conclusion to Mangog's siege of Asgard.
description.24: Ben Grimm makes the ultimate sacrifice to save the woman he loves. Will Alicia Masters be safe from the Android Man? Sue's pregnancy raises concern for mother and baby.
description.25: After collapsing in the middle of the street last issue, Spider-Man is taken into police custody!
description.26: Behold! The Vision appears suddenly from the mist, towering over the Avengers in this captivating cover by John Buscema.
description.27: When a group of spies make off with SHIELD's plans for their next-gen Life Model Decoy prototype, Cap springs into action to get the plans back!
description.29: Spider-Man battles the Vulture in the skies of New York! But with an arm injury cramping the Wallcrawler's style, duking it out with Adrian Toomes won't be an easy feat!
description.30: The new Avengers take on the original Avengers! It's a time-travel battle for the ages that involves two teams of the Earth's Mightiest Heroes. And what part does Dr. Doom play in this battle of the Avengers?
description.31: Captain America must re-live the most painful memory from his past; the death of Bucky Barnes. The Avengers team reunites with Cap, and discovers Dr. Doom's time machine.
description.32: Captain America battles Batroc the Leaper!
description.33: The Jester threatens to reveal Daredevil's secret identity...on the George Washington Bridge! With such a public outing at stake, Matt Murdock acts recklessly in his bid for control. NYPD vs. Daredevil! But why is the hero being hunted by the law?
description.34: Tony Stark is kidnapped into by a time-traveling soldier and brought to the future to be executed for a crime he has yet to create. Can the unarmed playboy convince the High Council that he is innocent?
description.36: Balder finds himself in deep trouble after rejecting the love of Karnilla Queen of Norn. "Hell hath no fury like"...you know the rest. Thor goes into battle with Mangog, the demonic creature intent on bringing Ragnarok to Asgard. When the God of Thunder is joined by the Warriors Three, will the scales of victory at last be tipped in Asgard's favor?
description.38: Reed Richards succeeds in reverting Ben Grimm back to normal...and now, the Thing is no more! But the timing couldn't be worse- the Wizard launches an attack on the FF, and the team is without its primary muscle! Plus, dangerous complications threaten Sue's pregnancy!
description.40: Dormammu has Strange, Clea, and Victoria locked up with no way out!
description.41: Watch out for Tiger Shark in his FIRST ever appearance!
description.42: Hulk vs. Mandarin! The Jade Giant is transported to the secret lair of the diabolical despot, and is immediately thrown into the deadliest gauntlet he's ever faced!
description.43: Failing to carry out the mission of infecting the people on Earth with the deadly bacteria, Ronan orders Mar-Vell to kill Logan!
description.44: The secret origin of S.H.I.E.L.D. - uncovered at last! How did the peacekeeping force come into existence, and what made them choose Nick Fury to lead them?
description.46: Nick Fury rushes to save one of his World War II pals, only to discovered he's been murdered at the Castle Ravenlock in Scotland!
description.47: Karen Page reaches a critical point in her career, and must decide whether her feelings for Murdock are enough to keep her at the law office. Daredevil continues his hunt for the vigilante, Jester. Guest-starring Captain America!
description.48: It's one disaster after another! After reverting Happy Hogan back to his normal self, Tony Stark must face the Unicorn! Can the Invincible Iron Man defeat the Unicorn and his deadly horn?
description.50: Mangog continues to storm Asgard to as his plot of revenge thickens. Could this be the coming of Ragnarok as Odin predicted? Thor fights against Asgard's End of Days, but the battle may well be out of his hands!
description.52: Trapped in the Microverse- at the hands of Psycho-Man! The Silver Surfer may have safely returned to Earth, but Reed, Johnny and Ben are still locked in battle against a megalomaniacal foe. Meanwhile, the threat of Galactus looms ever larger.
description.53: It's not often that Spider-Man has to break up a fight between two super villains. But this time it's Vulture against Vulture!
description.54: The Avengers are held captive by the Crimson Cowl, disguised as Jarvis! Plus, Ultron and Whirlwind escape during a fight with the Masters of Evil!
description.55: Captain America agrees to take on a group of next-gen Life Model Decoys in order to test their capabilities.
description.57: Silver Surfer's origin on Zenn-La revealed here!
description.58: Doctor Strange's quest to find the missing Clea makes an unexpected twist when he discovers that Dormammu is BACK!
description.60: Attuma, the barbarian warlord, aims to take over the city of Atlantis!
description.61: The super-slugfest between the Hulk and the Missing Link continues! But the battle takes a startling turn when the pair of behemoths are captured mid-battle by Yuri Brevlov and his team of Soviet spies!
description.62: Captain Marvel battles his conflicts between being a Kree soldier and his compassion for humanity.
description.63: When Nightmare hijacks the Ancient One's dreams, Doctor Strange rushes into his master's mind after the villain!
description.64: The Plant Man unleashes his monster onto the world, none other than the Leviathan!
description.65: The new mayoral candidate, Richard Raleigh has a strange hold over the masses of New York City. But simmering beneath the urbane exterior is something far more sinister and Peter Parker is the only one that notices...
description.66: The Hulk throws down with a mysterious creature known only as the Missing Link! What is the origin of this Cro-Magnon menace? And what exactly are Rick Jones and Glenn Talbot up to during all this?
description.67: FROM THE ASHES OF DEFEAT! Defeated, Captain Marvel gets even and reveals the Super Skrull's identity and sends him packing back to space.
description.68: Medusa has come to Earth on a goodwill mission on behalf of the Inhumans. But is that's the case, why is she slugging it out with Spidey?
description.69: Jarvis, Iron Man's loyal butler, betrays the Avengers for the new Masters of Evil. The Black Knight attempts to warn the Avengers about the security breach.
description.70: Agent 13-aka Sharon Carter-has been kidnapped by the Red Skull. Only Cap can save her now!
description.71: A new villain comes out to play, and this one considers himself quite the jokester! Meet Jester, a maniacal thief filled to the brim with gimmicks and gadgets. Matt uses his 'twin brother alter ego' Mike Murdock to take down his most twisted foe yet!
description.72: In the aftermath of his battle with the Demolisher, Tony Stark race against the clock to create a new suite complete with a new lasting battery to keep his heart from failing. But things get extremely complicated when the Freak appears.
description.74: Thor nearly has Loki in the palm of defeat, until Odin shows up! What is this new threat against Asgard Odin speaks of? And will the God of Thunder allow Loki to escape his grasp yet again? Guest-starring Karnilla the Norn Queen!
description.76: Journey to Sub-Atomica! Reed, Johnny and Ben travel through the Microverse to bring back the Silver Surfer. The crew finds Silver Surfer, all right...and a heap of particulate problems!
description.77: Once she stood among them as a member of the Frightful Four. Now, "the Magnificent Medusa" must face a deadly trio: the Trapster, Sandman, AND the Wizard!
description.78: Nick is joined by Jimmy Woo as they face off against the devious humanoid Centurius!
description.81: The Sub-Mariner must battle Triton of the Inhumans, but is it all a set-up?
description.82: Bruce Banner - prisoner of the USA! But even being held by the government can't help Bruce when he's abducted by the Rhino!
description.83: The Super Skrull returns to prove himself worthy to the emperor by plotting to kill Captain Marvel in exchange for the emperor's daughter.
description.84: As an agent of S.H.I.E.L.D. Nick Fury has always been getting himself into unbelievable situations, but this cover by Jim Steranko really takes the cake!
description.85: Trapped in his own hell, Daredevil's hope for escape looks bleak. But fear is where DD thrives, and this predicament is no exception! Foggy runs afoul of the wrong super villain. Who is the Exterminator? Karen and Matt talk about Daredevil's final demise.
description.86: One of Tony Starks many competitors seek to put an end to the Iron Man's fame. To prove that the Iron Man suite is nothing but a pile of mechanical junk, Drexel Cord will build a bigger and more destructive suite! Enter the Demolisher!
description.88: Someone has stolen the Thunder God's hammer! Mysteries abound, as the mighty Thor must track down the thief of the mightier Mjolnir! Plus, Lady Sif incurs an injury.
description.90: Galactus strengthens his resolve to find the missing Silver Surfer...and Reed, Ben and Johnny are trapped in the crossfire! The three heroes must face off against their doppelg'ngers....who have the cosmic powers of Galactus!
description.91: Gwen and George Stacy's lives hang in the balance! Meanwhile, Norman Osborn's memories slowly return.
description.92: It's the Avengers versus X-Men issue! Cyclops takes on Quicksilver.  Angel has a run-in with Wasp and Black Panther. In hand-to-fist combat who will be triumphant? Super powers or mutant abilities?
description.93: Captain America now has the device to control the fourth Sleeper robot, but the Red Skull has dispatched his minions to ensure the Sentinel of Liberty never has the chance to use it!
description.96: Daredevil goes to Limbo! The Unholy Three have been using their trans-dimensional T-ray to send innocents, and 'enemies', to an alternate dimension. Will DD be able to save Debbie Harris, and the rest of the victims, from a lifetime of purgatory? Enter the Organizer!
description.97: The First Issue of the First Iron Man ongoing series!  The Invincible Iron Man versus the menaces of Whiplash and A.I.M. Featuring Nick Fury and S.H.I.E.L.D.
description.99: Dr. Strange battles and defeats the imaginary creatures that Yandroth had sent against him in the Dimension of Dreams.

7.text: While Iceman languishes in Mesmero's prison, Lorna is experimented on to awaken her full, horrible potential!

10.text: Scorpio returns and successfully traps Nick Fury, who was scheduled to attend the unveiling of a new and improved LMD. With Fury his captive, Scorpio uses a machine to make a perfect casting of his face which he then wears as a mask to impersonate him and attend the unveiling in his place.

23.text: Iceman and Lorna versus Mesmero and the Demi-Men!

26.text: Mr. Hyde thinks he's tough, and he is - maybe even tough enough to fight the Avengers! But a greater power threatens the Earth itself, which suddenly has a lot fewer people on it!
Behold! The Vision appears suddenly from the mist, towering over the Avengers in this captivating cover by John Buscema.

28.text: Reprinting tales from Not Brand Echh #1-5! Tired of lazily put together "Best of" Compilations? Well look no further than right over here! Welcome to "The Worst of Not Brand Echh!"

31.text: Captain America must re-live the most painful memory from his past; the death of Bucky Barnes. The Avengers team reunites with Cap, and discovers Dr. Doom’s time machine.

37.text: Cyclops and Marvel Girl! What waits...within the Hive?

39.text: The first flight (and appearance) of Phantom Eagle, ace American fighter pilot of WWI!

51.text: The X-Men in the mystery of the Maha Yogi!

56.text: The Puppet Mister has gained complete and utter control of The Inedible Bulk and orders him to attack Prince No-More, the Sunk-Mariner! Totally not a parody of Tales to Astonish #100 or anything like that...promise.

75.text: The Juggernaut does battle with the X-Men in an effort to avenge himself upon Charles Xavier. But how will Juggernaut react when he learns of Xavier's death?

79.text: Doctor Strange’s origin issue! How did renowned surgeon Stephen Strange become the Master of Mystic Arts? All is revealed through a dreamy flashback. The Ancient One summons their most disciplined student.

84.text: As an agent of S.H.I.E.L.D. Nick Fury has always been getting himself into unbelievable situations, but this cover by Jim Steranko really takes the cake!

89.text: It's Cyclops versus Quicksilver for the fate of the X-Men!

94.text: Forbush Man tries to join the ranks of...the mighty Revengers!
